---
GRACEFUL LIBRARY:

Here are some functions that can go in a graceful library.
On a UNIX system, to learn what the underlying code is
supposed to do, remove the leading "g" and the ending ".c"
in the filename and invoke man to read about it.

For example, to learn what the function gutimes() in the
file gutimes.c, is supposed to do, give the command

   man utimes

---
On a UNIX system, try the following commands:

   make              // to make the library

   ar -t g_lib.a     // to see the titles of the functions in the library

   nm g_lib.a        // to see more information
